<br>
&quot;The Amazons have Ares on their side.&quot; She noted. Though she and Ares had many quarrels, he was the God of war as she the Goddess of such. She knew his powers and devotion to his daughters. <br>
<br>
&quot;It's a shame that the others,&quot; speaking of the Gods &quot;will regret these moments here. For they know not how badly they could fail.&quot;<br>
<br>
She too knew that some amazons would be hurt, or lost. But she had faith that they would still live in their nation. Once a God is destroyed in spirit, he is lost forever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=royalfogstone>Royal Fogstone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/15/01 6:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gods</span><hr size=1> (Has everyone posted, or entered the subject so that we may start the war?) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/15/01 6:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gods</span><hr size=1>  [Hold your horses, and let us have some fun.]<br>
<br>
 Dawn grinned, although it couldn't be seen, she grinned from ear to ear. Crimsons travelling to the center of the battlefield, at the appearence of the god. Then a sidelong glance was given to Hippolyte, and then a shrug of her shoulders in mild consideration of what had just happened infront of them. <br>
<br>
 Then her eyes went to Sartha, her mask lifted from her face, and for a few moments, it was the true side of Dawn that showed. There was not hint of worry, or doubt, pure force and guts, the true Dawn, no blood lust.<br>
<br>
 &quot;I'll see you on the otherside.. no matter what side it is. I'll see you, sister.&quot;<br>
<br>
 There was no amazon language to hide her feeling, it was the bond they had. Not just amazon but beyond that world..through everything.<br>
<br>
 The mask was then placed back over her face, the amazon shifted slightly in the saddle. She could sense them all, Athena, Ares, Hera.<br>
